Why?<br>
Whats one of the biggest problems we have grouping?<br>
&quot;Pets break mez!&quot;<br>
Answer is to use gnoll hide lariats, they stun, stunned mobs don't attack pet, so you can /pet back off fast so they can be re-mezzed etc! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
If you can get pet dex buffed it does seem to increase proc rate. On a malosied mob, an air pet with 2 whips will stun mobs up to 50% of the fight! (seen that in the Hole, elemental warrior was stunned most of a fight between pet and barb warriro's slams) Generally 10-20% of the time mobs are stunned I'd say. That's a huge saving in damage and survivablity for you/your group. When grouped turn /pet taunt off or it will get aggroed on and destroyed too often (you to).<br>
  Cast Expedience/Velocity on pet so it can get back off mobs faster, and get to them.<br>
  Doing this makes mages more appreciated by chanters,and every one else as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
  If you can get skills up high, making and carrying some banded armour is an idea, from tests I reckon it increases pet's survivability a fair bit, total of +56 AC from a full set. Perhaps 15%+ harder to kill old Jibober, and that DOES make a difference soloing or when your group may face serious threats and your pet ends up tanking.<br>
